src.inference.domains.carpark package¶

Submodules¶

src.inference.domains.carpark.carpark_board module¶

Board and move primitives for Rush Hour (car-park) tasks.

This module exposes canonicalization and validation helpers for Rush sequences. It intentionally avoids any dataset I/O or LLM-specific logic so that core state/operation code stays easy to test and re-use.

src.inference.domains.carpark.carpark_cli module¶

Command-line entrypoint for carpark (Rush Hour) inference.

This module is responsible only for CLI wiring. It invokes the unified carpark runner, which in turn calls into src.inference.domains.carpark.carpark_core for dataset loading and inference logic.

src.inference.domains.carpark.carpark_cli.main(argv: Sequence[str] | None = None) → None[source]¶

CLI entrypoint used by python -m src.inference.domains.carpark.carpark_cli.

src.inference.domains.carpark.carpark_core module¶

Thin compatibility/shim module for Rush Hour (car-park) inference.

The implementation for two-pass inference now lives in src.inference.domains.carpark.carpark_solver and the dataset loader in src.inference.domains.carpark.carpark_data. This module keeps the original public API surface so that existing imports and task-registry dotted paths continue to work.

Load a Rush Hour dataset and ensure required columns are present.

src.inference.domains.carpark.carpark_core.run_inference_on_split(**kwargs) → None[source]¶

Public wrapper matching the signature used by unified runners.

This function adapts flat keyword arguments from the unified CLI into a CarparkInferenceConfig and runs the full two-pass inference loop.

Parameters:

kwargs – Keyword-only arguments including split_name, examples, tokenizer, model, step, outdir, and common sampling options (batch_size, num_samples, temperature, top_p, entropy_mode, eos_ids, two_pass, second_pass_phrase, second_pass_use_sample_idx, think_cap, answer_cap).

Returns:

None. Results are written to a JSONL file under outdir.

src.inference.domains.carpark.carpark_data module¶

Dataset loading and record helpers for Rush Hour (car-park) inference.

This module hosts the pieces that turn raw dataset rows into the normalized structures consumed by src.inference.domains.carpark.carpark_solver.

src.inference.domains.carpark.carpark_solver module¶

Two-pass batch inference for Rush Hour (car-parking) using Qwen2.5-style chat LMs that produce: <think> … </think><answer> … </answer>.

This version supports resume/fill behaviour: - If the output JSONL already contains some rows for an example_id, we detect

which sample_idx values are present and write ONLY the missing ones.

  • After a run, every example will have exactly –num_samples rows.

Module contents¶

Rush Hour (car-park) domain modules.

The full inference stack—including solver, dataset loader, CLI wiring, and helper utilities—now lives under this subpackage.
